<div class="wrapper">
	<div class="container" id="main">
		<article id="content">
			<header>
				<h2>Prayer room facilities</h2>
			</header>

      <div class="block">
        <h3>Medical School Library - Room CLG30</h3>
        <h4>Facilities</h4>
        <ul>
          <li>
            Brothers and sisters section (separated in 2 sides by large
            curtains, entrance for both is the same) however facilities
            separate for both.
          </li>
          <li>Prayer mats stored in a chest of draws</li>
          <li>
            Islamic books e.g. copies of the Quran (including English
            translated versions), Islamic educational books,
            Islamic history books etc...
          </li>
          <li>CDs with list of different duas</li>
          <li>Chairs</li>
        </ul>

        <h4>Directions/location</h4>
        <p>
          Located on the lower ground floor in Room CLG30. From the ground floor,
          take the stairs downstairs (or use lift option '-1') then take left through
          double doors. Then turn left and follow around. You will see a sign
          directing towards the prayer room. Follow sign until you come to the
          room as shown in the picture below. For wudhu, continue walking past
          the prayer room and take first right, female toilets will then be to
          your left and male toilets to your right.
        </p>
        <div class="gallery gallery-2">
          <%= tag :img, :src => "/images/prayer-room-locations/med-entrance.jpg" %>
          <%= tag :img, :src => "/images/prayer-room-locations/med-room.jpg" %>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="block">
        <h3>Mech Eng room S10B (brothers only)</h3>
        <h4>Facilities</h4>
        <ul>
          <li>Small table and a couple of chairs</li>
          <li>Prayer mats (already laid out)</li>
        </ul>

        <h4>Direction/location</h4>
        <p>
          If you are coming from Selly Oak then take the first entrance into
          the mechanical engineering building. Upon entering take the stairs
          to go up on your right and then go straight until you come to a
          corridor on your left with a sign above which says
          'Advanced machining/manufacturing processes lab sign'.
          There are stairs going up, go up the stairs (for toilets go downstairs
          as shown by sign directions).
          Keep going until you get to the 2nd floor.
        </p>
        <p>
          On the 2nd floor, go through the brown double doors to your left then
          go straight and take a right. Follow the corridor around until you get
          to room S10B (it is at the very end).
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="block">
        <h3>Chemical Engineering</h3>
        <h4>Facilities</h4>
        <ul>
          <li>Prayer mat/carpet</li>
          <li>1 chair</li>
        </ul>

        <h4>Direction locations</h4>
        <p>
          Upon entering the chemical engineering building through the front
          entrance take a right and go through the blue double doors, then
          walk straight around the corridor until you get to stairs that are
          going up. Next to the stairs there is an empty space. Go there and
          under the stairs. There is a chair with a prayer mat on it.
        </p>
        <p>For the nearest toilets follow the directions that are hanging around the walls and ceiling within the building.</p>

        <div class="gallery gallery-2">
          <%= tag :img, :src => "/images/prayer-room-locations/chem-eng-1.jpg" %>
          <%= tag :img, :src => "/images/prayer-room-locations/chem-eng-2.jpg" %>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="block">
        <h3>Computer Science</h3>
        <h4>Facilities</h4>
        <ul>
          <li>Prayer mats</li>
          <li>1 chair</li>
          <li>For both brothers and sisters</li>
        </ul>

        <h4>Directions/location</h4>
        <p>
          Upon entering the computer science building, take a right and go
          through the brown double doors which have a sign for the 'Stairs'
          above them. Walk up the stairs until you get to the top floor.
          On your right there will be a sign about the prayer mats and below
          the sign are the prayers mats and signs. For the nearest toilets
          follow the signs.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="block">
        <h3>Chaplaincy</h3>
        <h4>Facilities</h4>
        <ul>
          <li>Qurans</li>
          <li>Prayer mats</li>
          <li>Chairs and tables</li>
        </ul>

        <h4>Directions/location</h4>
        <p>
          Take the main entrance and then go through the brown double doors
          to your left that are next to the reception. For toilets/wudhu
          facilities take the stairs going downstairs and then take a right
          at the bottom of the stairs and follow the signs.
        </p>

        <h4>Entrance</h4>
        <p>
          For jumuah, sisters take the entrance on the side of the chaplaincy
          and brothers take the main entrance. Outside jumuah times, the entrance
          is the same.
        </p>
        <p>
          <strong>NOTE:</strong> The facility may not always be available due to other events occurring within the room.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="block">
        <h3>The Guild of Students</h3>
        <h4>Facilities (brothers and sisters side)</h4>
        <ul>
          <li>Qurans</li>
          <li>Islamic books</li>
          <li>Microwave</li>
          <li>Kettle</li>
          <li>Book rest desks</li>
        </ul>

        <h4>Directions/locations</h4>
        <p>
          When walking towards the guild from the clock tower, take the entrance
          that is next to the atm machine on your right. Walk straight on and
          around the pillar in the centre of the corridor and take the stairs
          up to the next floor. Sisters take the left through the double doors
          and brothers take a right and walk around until they come to the room
          with a shoe rack outside, that is the entrance to the prayer room for
          brothers. For the nearest toilets/wudhu facilities, follow the signs
          or ask a brother/sister inside the prayer room.
        </p>
      </div>
		</article>
	</div>
</div>
